dc_title_s: Transportation Planning Road Centerlines (MPO) Dane County, 2018
dc_description_s: This data layer represents road centerlines with Transportation Planning Board attributes for Dane County, Wisconsin in 2018. [Dane County Road Centerlines with MATPB attributes designed for Transportation Planning purposes. MATPB attributes include: Planned and Existing On-Street Bike Facilities Functional Class Biking Suitability Shoulder Width Truck Routes National Highway System (NHS) Median Type Sidewalks Lanes Primary Direction The reminder of the attributes are from the DCLIO centerline file. Directional Coding Note: Divided streets are generally coded the same for both primary and opposite direction. For example, a bike lane on only one direction is coded as showing a bike lane in both directions. Updated: 11/2018
dc_creator_sm: City of Madison - Metropolitan Planning Organization (MPO)
uw_supplemental_s: Archived dataset at UW-Madison. For the most current version of this data please visit: https://data-cityofmadison.opendata.arcgis.com/
